## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of sources and the scope of the search. The findings are based on a selection of essays and educational resources, which may not cover all perspectives or the latest developments in research ethics. Additionally, the reliance on secondary sources may introduce bias based on the authors' interpretations and the contexts in which the studies were conducted. Further research could involve primary data collection and interviews with researchers to gain deeper insights into ethical transgressions in social research.

